Enum SelectReport

Serializable, Comparable<SelectReport>
public enum SelectReport
extends Enum<SelectReport>

The SELECT REPORT field is a member of the ReportLunsCDB and specifies the types of logical unit addresses that shall be reported.

The field is two bits long.

Author:
Andreas Ergenzinger

Enum Constant Detail

SELECTED_ADDRESSING_METHODS

public static final SelectReport SELECTED_ADDRESSING_METHODS
The list shall contain the logical units accessible to the I_T nexus with the following addressing methods (see SAM):
  1. AddressMethod.LOGICAL_UNIT_ADDRESSING_METHOD,
  2. AddressMethod.PERIPHERAL_DEVICE_ADDRESSING_METHOD, and
  3. AddressMethod.FLAT_SPACE_ADDRESSING_METHOD.
If there are no logical units, the LUN LIST LENGTH field shall be zero.

WELL_KNOWN_LUNS_ONLY

public static final SelectReport WELL_KNOWN_LUNS_ONLY
The list shall contain only well known logical units, if any. If there are no well known logical units, the LUN LIST LENGTH field shall be zero.

ALL

public static final SelectReport ALL
The list shall contain all logical units accessible to the I_T nexus.
